In [11]:
# Dropping the column 'unnamed: 0'
data_raw.drop(columns=['Unnamed: 0'], inplace=True)
In [12]:
# Renaming the column 'Data', 'Genre', 'Countries' and 'Local' to 'Date', 'Gender', 'Country' and 'City'
data_raw.rename(columns={'Data':'Date', 'Genre':'Gender', 'Countries':'Country', 'Local':'City'}, inplace=True)
In [13]:
# Replacing the values in the 'Country', 'City', 'Accident Level' and 'Potential Accident Level' columns with integers
columnValueMapping = {
    'Country': {'Country_01': 1, 'Country_02': 2, 'Country_03': 3},
    'City': {'Local_01': 1, 'Local_02': 2, 'Local_03': 3, 'Local_04': 4, 'Local_05': 5, 'Local_06': 6, 'Local_07': 7, 'Local_08': 8, 'Local_09': 9, 'Local_10': 10, 'Local_11': 11, 'Local_12': 12},
    'Accident Level': {'I': 1, 'II': 2, 'III': 3, 'IV': 4, 'V': 5},
    'Potential Accident Level': {'I': 1, 'II': 2, 'III': 3, 'IV': 4, 'V': 5, 'VI': 6}
}

data_raw.replace(columnValueMapping, inplace=True)

plt.title("Accidents Per Year",fontsize=20,fontweight="bold")
plt.xlabel("\nYear", fontsize=15, fontweight="bold")
plt.ylabel("\nNumber of Accidents", fontsize=15, fontweight="bold")
plt.tight_layout()

There is data for 2 years, i.e, 2016 and 2017. However, it can be seen that there are lesser number of accidents reported in the year 2017. This could be because the data is not present for the entire year of 2017.

plt.title("Accidents in the year 2017", fontsize=20, fontweight="bold")
plt.xlabel("\nMonth", fontsize=15, fontweight="bold")
plt.ylabel("\nNumber of Accidents", fontsize=15, fontweight="bold")
plt.tight_layout()

From the above two plots, it can be seen that:</br>

a. In the month of January 2017, there were more accidents than in the month of January 2016</br> b. In the month of March 2017, there were lesser accidents than in the month of March 2016</br> c. In the month of May 2017, there were lesser accidents than in the month of May 2016</br> d. In the month of June 2017, there were lesser accidents than in the month of June 2016</br> e. In the month of July 2017, there were lesser accidents than in the month of July 2016</br>

This decline in the number of accidents in the year 2017 can be further investigated to understand what preventive measures were taken by the companies.

4. NLP Pre-processing¶

In [48]:
# Defining a function to lemmatize the text
stop = set(stopwords.words('english'))

def preprocess_text(text):
    corpus=[]
    lem=WordNetLemmatizer()
    for news in text:
        words=[w for w in word_tokenize(news) if (w not in stop)]
        words=[lem.lemmatize(w) for w in words if len(w)>2]
        words = [''.join(c for c in s if c not in string.punctuation) for s in words if s]
        words = [word.lower() for word in words]
        words = [word for word in words if word.isalpha()]
        corpus.append(words)  
    return corpus

from sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity
import random

def response(user_response):
    robo_response=''
    #user_response = "What happened to Mr. Emerson?"

    desc_text = data_raw['Processed_Description'].to_list()
    desc_text.append(user_response)

    tfidf_vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer(ngram_range=(1,2))
    desc_vect = tfidf_vectorizer.fit_transform(desc_text)
    #user_vect =  tfidf_vectorizer.fit_transform(user_response)

    vals = cosine_similarity(desc_vect[-1], desc_vect)
    idx=vals.argsort()[0][-2]
    flat = vals.flatten()
    flat.sort()
    req_tfidf = flat[-2]
    if(req_tfidf==0):
        robo_response=robo_response+"I am sorry! I don't understand you"
        #print(robo_response)
        desc_text.remove(user_response)
        return robo_response
    else:

        #print(robo_response)

        elif(help(user_response)!=None):
            return (help(user_response))
        
        elif(bye(user_response)!=None):

from tkinter import *

BG_WHITE = "#FFFFFF"#"#ABB2B9"
BG_COLOR = "#17202A"
TEXT_COLOR="#EAECEE"
BG_GRAY = "#ABB2B9"
FONT="Helvetica 14"
FONT_BOLD = "Helvetica 13 bold"
BOT_NAME = "MERCY"

class ChatApplication:
    
    def __init__(self):
        self.window = Tk()
        self._setup_main_window()
        
    def run(self):
        self.window.mainloop()
        
    
    def _setup_main_window(self):
        self.window.title("Chat")
        self.window.resizable(width=False,height=False)
        self.window.configure(width=1400,height=800,bg=BG_COLOR)
        
        #HEAD LABEL
        head_label=Label(self.window,bg=BG_COLOR,fg=TEXT_COLOR,text="WELCOME",
                         font="FONT_BOLD",pady=10)
        head_label.place(relwidth=1)
        
        #tiny divider
        line = Label(self.window,width=450,bg = BG_GRAY)
        line.place(relwidth=1,rely=0.07,relheight=0.012)
        
        #text widget
        self.text_widget = Text(self.window,width=20,height=2,bg="#008080",fg=TEXT_COLOR,
                                font=FONT,padx=5,pady=5)
        self.text_widget.place(relheight=0.745,relwidth = 1,rely=0.08)
        self.text_widget.configure(cursor="arrow",state=DISABLED)
        
#         #scroll bar
#         scrollbar = Scrollbar(self.text_widget)
#         scrollbar.place(relheight=1,relx=0.947)
#         scrollbar.configure(command=self.text_widget.yview)
        
        #bottom label
        bottom_label = Label(self.window,bg=BG_GRAY,height=80)
        bottom_label.place(relwidth=1,rely=0.825)
        
        #message entry box
        self.msg_entry = Entry(bottom_label,bg = "#808000",fg=TEXT_COLOR,font=FONT)
        self.msg_entry.place(relwidth=0.74,relheight=0.06,rely=0.008,relx=0.011)
        self.msg_entry.focus()
        self.msg_entry.bind("<Return>",self._on_enter_pressed)
        
        #send button
        send_button = Button(bottom_label,text="Send",font=FONT_BOLD,width=20,bg="#0000FF",
                             command=lambda: self._on_enter_pressed(None))
        send_button.place(relx=0.77,rely=0.008,relheight=0.06,relw=0.22)
        
    
    def _on_enter_pressed(self,event):
        msg = self.msg_entry.get()
        self._insert_message(msg,"You")
    
    def _insert_message(self,msg,sender):
        if not msg:
            return
        
        self.msg_entry.delete(0,END)
        
        #display user's message
        msg1= f"{sender}:{msg}\n\n"
        self.text_widget.configure(state=NORMAL)
        self.text_widget.insert(END,msg1)
        self.text_widget.configure(state=DISABLED)
        
        #display bot's message
        #text = "Hi!,My name is Mercy and I am kind enough to prevent you from harmful accidents:)"
        bot_response = bot_reply(msg)
        msg1= f"{BOT_NAME}:{bot_response}\n\n"
        self.text_widget.configure(state=NORMAL)
        self.text_widget.insert(END,msg1)
        self.text_widget.configure(state=DISABLED)
        
        self.text_widget.see(END)

Future scope of study¶

  1. Collect more data</br> Currently there are 425 records. This count is not sufficient to train the models. Having more data will allow better accuracy of results</br>

  2. Collect additional information about the accidents</br> Additional information about the equipment that led to the accident, such as equipment name, voltage passed to the equipment, temperature of the equipment at the time of accident, will greatly help in predicting a wider range of incidents and the accuracy of the model will also be higher

  3. Use Named Entity Recognition</br> Having NER will allow us identify equipments that led to accident or the persons involved in the accident

  4. Sentiment analysis</br> Sentiment analysis can be used to detect the severity of the accident description and assign relevant accident level or potential accident level</br>
